modules.description: Provides functions for manipulating large byte sequences, including slicing, copying, and concatenating. Works with the bigstring data type, which is optimized for handling large amounts of binary data. Used for efficient network data processing and file I/O operations.

The module offers low-level manipulation of large, mutable character arrays, including creation, slicing, copying, and efficient conversions between bigstrings and types like bytes, strings, and buffers. It handles operations such as case transformation, trimming, and character property checks, leveraging bigarrays of unsigned 8-bit characters for high-performance memory management. This is particularly useful in scenarios requiring direct memory access, large-scale data processing, or interoperability with C-based I/O systems.
